cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CY 

This paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to analyze sentiments and emotions of users on medical forums. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with NLP and its applications. The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as CNN and SVM, which fall under sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques to crawl data from medical forums, which falls under sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with analyzing social media data, which falls under sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
